{
  "page": "Queen Rhaenys",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For others with the same name, see <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys\" title=\"Rhaenys\">Rhaenys</a>.</div>\n<p>The <i><b>Queen Rhaenys</b></i> was a war galley in <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a>'s fleet and a flagship of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Velaryon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It was named after either Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>, one of the wives of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a>, or Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>, the so-called Queen Who Never Was and the wife of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Queen_Rhaenys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <i>Queen Rhaenys</i> was Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Velaryon</a>'s flagship when <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a> joined Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gedmund_Peake\" title=\"Gedmund Peake\">Gedmund Peake</a> against <a href=\"/index.php/Racallio_Ryndoon\" title=\"Racallio Ryndoon\">Racallio Ryndoon</a>, the self-proclaimed <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Narrow_Sea\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King of the Narrow Sea\">King of the Narrow Sea</a>, during the <a href=\"/index.php/Daughters%27_War\" title=\"Daughters&#39; War\">Daughters' War</a>. When the Velaryons joined the <a href=\"/index.php/Royal_fleet\" title=\"Royal fleet\">royal fleet</a>, Gedmund sent <a href=\"/index.php/Ned_Bean\" title=\"Ned Bean\">Ned Bean</a> to the <i>Queen Rhaenys</i> to take command of the Velaryon ships. Alyn left Gedmund Great-Axe and Blackbean behind at <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a>, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Alyn%27s_attack\" title=\"Lord Alyn&#39;s attack\">Lord Alyn's attack</a> on the <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavosi</a> fleet in the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a>, Alyn rammed the great dromond <i><a href=\"/index.php/Grand_Defiance\" title=\"Grand Defiance\">Grand Defiance</a></i> with the <i>Queen Rhaenys</i>, earning himself the nickname of Oakenfist.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Alyn was rewarded with a <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a> replica of his ship by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Unwin_Peake\" title=\"Unwin Peake\">Unwin Peake</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Queen_Rhaenys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - War and Peace and Cattle Shows.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404214940\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.034 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.060 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 417/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8698/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1998/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1036/2097152 bytes